title: Settings still single-provider; legacy fields trap multi-mode off
updated_at: "2026-07-15T05:49:06Z"
---
## Problem
Settings still lead with single-provider controls (`provider`, OpenCode sub-provider, account index, display name, credentials path). In `ProfileController.isLegacySingleInstance()`, any non-empty `credentialsPath`, non-empty `displayName`, or `provider !== "claude"` forces legacy filtering. Existing widgets (or casual Configure edits) therefore never get the multi-provider multi-account dashboard even when discovery would find many profiles.

## Location
contents/ui/configGeneral.qml:61-128
ProfileController isLegacySingleInstance()

## Suggested fix
Split UI into “Multi-profile (default)” vs “Legacy single profile.” In multi mode, hide/ignore `provider`/`credentialsPath` as primary controls; clear or stop writing fields that force legacy mode. Document that multi-profile requires empty `credentialsPath`/`displayName` and default `provider=claude` until migration is explicit.

## Source
Review ff0a2eec Issue 4 — settings page doesn’t work well for multi-provider multi-account